<h2>TB-500 Dosing: Loading and Maintenance Protocols</h2>

<p>TB-500 dosing typically follows a two-phase approach. A loading phase builds up systemic levels, followed by a reduced maintenance schedule.</p>

<table class="tbl">
<thead><tr><th>Phase</th><th>Dose</th><th>Frequency</th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>Loading</strong></td><td class="g">2&ndash;2.5 mg</td><td>Twice per week</td><td>4&ndash;6 weeks</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Aggressive loading</strong></td><td class="y">5 mg</td><td>Twice weekly (first 2 weeks)</td><td>2 weeks, then standard</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Maintenance</strong></td><td class="g">2&ndash;2.5 mg</td><td>Once every 1&ndash;2 weeks</td><td>2&ndash;3 months</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<div class="g2">
  <div class="mc">
    <h4 style="color:var(--blue);">Acute Injuries</h4>
    <p>Start the loading phase as soon as possible after the injury occurs. Standard 4-week loading at 2&ndash;2.5 mg twice weekly, then transition to maintenance.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="mc">
    <h4 style="color:var(--teal);">Chronic Injuries</h4>
    <p>The loading phase may need to extend to 6 full weeks before transitioning to maintenance. Some users run longer maintenance cycles for stubborn conditions.</p>
  </div>
</div>

